text.tspan: Supplementary Figure S4: Pacbio longread analysis

tspan.tspan: Capture and reverse transcription of mRNA molecules with barcoded (DropSeq) beads (top) can lead to the production of different
cDNA species (bottom). The expected product should contain Template Switch Oligo (TSO) sequence, mRNA, polyT, and the bead-
side primer handle composed of SMART primer sequence + AC dinucleotide (green, rounded box). Longread analysis revealed
byproducts lacking polyT and cDNAs with tandem repeats of primer sequences (concatamers).
annotates pacbio reads against a catalog of known cDNA building blocks. It then analyzes their presence/absence and ordering to
reveal common signatures (left, log-scaled x-axis). The dominant cDNA species in this library were composed of tandem occurrences
of the SMART primer sequence (center, pale green) and the bead_start (SMART+AC) sequence. Only ~1.5% of pacbio reads featured
an unrepeated bead-side primer handle (center, bright green, "bead-related"). Of these, the vast majority lack polyT (right, yellow),
which would be expected for polyA-mRNA capture.
) Similar to B) but for an improved run. Here, almost all reads feature the bead
handle (center, bright green), of which almost all furthermore carry polyT as well (right, dark green).
